  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "What is عطف البيان?",
      "titleArabic": "تعريف عطف البيان",
      "content": [
        "عطف البيان is a tābic (follower) that clarifies the word before it, like how a proper noun clarifies a common noun.",
        "For example: جَاءَ الْخَلِيفَةُ عُمَرُ (The caliph, Umar, came). Here عُمَرُ clarifies الْخَلِيفَةُ."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Clarifies the word it follows (متبوع)",
        "Must agree in case with the word it follows",
        "Often uses a proper noun to clarify a common noun",
        "Similar to البدل but has subtle differences"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ الْخَلِيفَةُ عُمَرُ", "english": "The caliph Umar came" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ الشَّاعِرَ الْمُتَنَبِّيَ", "english": "I saw the poet Al-Mutanabbi" },
        { "arabic": "قَرَأْتُ سُورَةَ الْفَاتِحَةِ", "english": "I read Surat Al-Fatiha" },
        { "arabic": "زُرْتُ الإِمَامَ أَحْمَدَ", "english": "I visited Imam Ahmad" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Difference from البدل",
      "titleArabic": "الفرق بين عطف البيان والبدل",
      "content": [
        "Both عطف البيان and البدل involve a following noun that relates to the first, but they differ in their relationship.",
        "In البدل, the second noun can replace the first in meaning. In عطف البيان, the second simply clarifies without replacement."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "البدل: The second can stand alone replacing the first",
        "عطف البيان: The second only clarifies, cannot replace",
        "عطف البيان often has جنس + proper noun structure",
        "Test: Can you remove the first word? If no → عطف البيان"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ أَخُوكَ زَيْدٌ (بدل)", "english": "Your brother Zaid came (بدل - Zaid can replace)" },
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ الْخَلِيفَةُ عُمَرُ (عطف بيان)", "english": "The caliph Umar came (عطف بيان - الخليفة needed)" },
        { "arabic": "هَذَا الصَّحَابِيُّ بِلَالٌ", "english": "This companion is Bilal" },
        { "arabic": "حَضَرَ الْمَلِكُ فَهْدٌ", "english": "King Fahd attended" }
      ]
    }
